title: Hyundai Grand i10 Nios - better than a Swift? | First Drive Review | Autocar India
description: The third generation of Hyundai's i10 mid-range hatchback has larger dimensions and a longer name. 'Nios' means more, and it certainly delivers on the name, but is that enough to give a strong enough fight to the Swift? Hormazd Sorabjee drives the Hyundai Grand i10 Nios to find out.
author: Autocar India

title: 2021 Maruti Suzuki Swift review - Better Performance? I Autocar India
description: The 2021 version of the Maruti Suzuki Swift has new engine technology. Has the power upgrade made a difference? What is the mileage of the new Swift? What are the other changes on the new Swift? What is the price of the 2021 Maruti Suzuki Swift?
author: Autocar India

title: Hyundai i20 N Line vs Volkswagen Polo GT TSI - Passing the baton | Comparison | Autocar India
description: In the blue corner is the Hyundai i20 N Line. In the red corner is the Volkswagen Polo GT TSI. Can the best driving Hyundai hatchback better the OG fun-to-drive hatchback? Saumil Shah and Nikhil Bhatia make case for their favourites.
author: Autocar India

title: 2022 Maruti Suzuki Baleno review - It’s all new! | AMT & Manual driven | Autocar India
description: The 2022 Maruti Baleno resembles the old one so much you could be forgiven for thinking it’s a facelift. The fact is, it’s all new! And among the changes, there's the AMT that comes in place of the old CVT auto. Renuka Kirpalani tells you all there is to know about in her 2022 Baleno review.
author: Autocar India

title: 2019 Small Car Comparo Review: Mazda3, Corolla, Golf, Focus, i30, Cerato, Civic, Astra, 308, Impreza
description:
Ford Focus v Holden Astra v Honda Civic v Hyundai i30 v Kia Cerato v Mazda 3 v Peugeot 308 v Subaru Impreza v Toyota Corolla v Volkswagen Golf

It's time. We've put the 10 most popular small cars together, priced between $30,000 and $40,000, to see which are most deserving of your attention.
author: Drive.com.au

title: EXCLUSIVE! 2021 Mercedes-Benz GLA review - Merc's baby SUV grows up | First Drive | Autocar India
description: Your wait for the new Mercedes-Benz GLA is almost over! Shapur Kotwal brings you the very first review of the gen 2 GLA in India.
author: Autocar India

title: 2020 Maruti Suzuki S-Cross Petrol review - A change of heart | First Drive | Autocar India
description: The long-awaited Maruti Suzuki S-Cross petrol is finally here as a replacement for the now-discontinued diesel version. Also new to the S-Cross line-up is an automatic gearbox option. Hormazd Sorabjee drives the S-Cross petrol automatic and manual to tell you if the crossover should be on your shopping list.
author: Autocar India

title: Maruti Suzuki S-Presso | First Drive Review | Autocar India
description: Maruti Suzuki are cashing in on the Indian buyers affinity for SUV’s with their latest offering the S-Presso. Renuka Kirpalani drives the car in Jodhpur to find out whether this budget car is worth buying. In this review she gives a detailed insight into the design, the interiors, the performance and the features along with details of the variants and price.
author: Autocar India

title: 2019 Maruti Suzuki Wagon R I First Drive Review I Autocar India
description: The freshly launched tall boy Wagon R is not just a face lift it is a completely new car. This time around it also gets the K12 1.2 litre engine. Renuka Kirpalani takes a test drive of both manual and AMT variants to tell you what you can expect from the all new Wagon R.
author: Autocar India

title: 2021 MG Astor review – Hello Astor! | First Drive | Autocar India
description: The MG Astor is the petrol version of the ZS EV we’re familiar with, and it’s here to rival the Hyundai Creta, Kia Seltos, Volkswagen Taigun, Skoda Kushaq and Nissan Kicks. Nikhil Bhatia experiences all the tech it has to offer and gets a first impression of what the new MG SUV is like to drive.
author: Autocar India

title: City vs Verna vs Ciaz vs Vento vs Rapid vs Yaris - The Best Sedan Is... | Comparison | Autocar India
description: The mid-size sedan segment has seen a lot of action in 2020 with new launches, facelifts and engine upgrades. But which is the pick of the segment? We've got the whole bunch together to find out. With us today are the fifth-gen Honda City, Hyundai Verna facelift, Volkswagen Vento TSI, Skoda Rapid TSI, Toyota Yaris and Maruti Suzuki Ciaz, and all of the cars are featured in their petrol-manual form.
author: Autocar India

title: 2020 Skoda Superb Facelift - Still want that German sedan? | First Drive Review | Autocar India
description: For 2020, the Skoda Superb has received a facelift and has also made the dramatic shift to petrol-only power. What's it like? Gavin D'Souza has the answer.
author: Autocar India

title: Skoda Slavia 1.5 TSI review - The ultimate enthusiast's sedan | First Drive | Autocar India
description: Hot on the heels of the 1.0 TSI Skoda are launching the 1.5 TSI. With Segment leading power figures, this is a sedan for those who love to drive. Renuka Kirpalani drives both manual and DSG in this review.
author: Autocar India

title: 2021 Volvo S60 review - Comfort zone | First Drive | Autocar India
description: The new Volvo S60 will finally go on sale in India in early 2021. Sergius Barretto drives one to tell you what's in store.

title: 2020 Honda City Review - Evolution or Revolution? | First Drive | Autocar India
description: The City is Honda's most important model in India and it will soon be launched in an all-new avatar. Interestingly, however, this is the first time the old City will continue to be sold alongisde the new one. As a result the new model has grown up significantly and as Gavin D'Souza and Sergius Barretto find out, there's a lot to be excited for with the new model.

title: 2022 Volkswagen Virtus - VW sedan to lure you away from Honda City & Skoda Slavia | Autocar India
description: The Volkswagen Virtus mid-size sedan is here to take on the Honda City and its cousin, the new Skoda Slavia. Sergius Barretto gives you an introduction to the exciting new VW.

title: 2020 Hyundai Verna Review - Facelift With Turbo Petrol Power | First Drive | Autocar India
description: With the Verna facelift, Hyundai has been really comprehensive. Not only does it get a distinctly new look, but it also gets new petrol and diesel engines, as well as a range-topping turbo-petrol with a DCT. Nikhil Bhatia drives it to tell you what's new.

title: 2019 Toyota Camry Hybrid | First Drive Review | Autocar India
description: The new, eighth-gen Toyota Camry Hybrid is not just bigger and more luxurious than before, it's got a heavily revised powertrain that promises to be vastly more fuel efficient. Gavin D'Souza drives it in Hyderabad to see what's new, and how it compares to other luxury sedans of a similar price.

title: 2020 Honda City vs Hyundai Verna - Diesel duel | Comparison | Autocar India
description: Looking for a diesel mid-sized sedan? Renuka Kirpalani lines up the two models of interest - the 2020 Honda City and the facelifted Hyundai Verna. Featured here are the Honda City ZX diesel and the Hyundai Verna diesel SX(O) MT.

title: 2021 Honda Amaze facelift - It's all in the details | First Drive | Autocar India
description: The Honda Amaze gets an update for 2021 and beyond. Nikhil Bhatia runs you through the changes and tells you the reasons to be interested in Honda's compact sedan.

title: Rolls-Royce Ghost review | luxury Rolls driven | Autocar
description: Here's a straightforward sensible car review of a straightforward sensible car. Well, these things are relative. This is the new Rolls-Royce Ghost and it is Rolls-Royce's entry-level saloon. Which still means it costs £208,000 and has a 6.6-litre V12 engine making 563bhp.

title: 2021 Mercedes-Benz S-Class review - Sit back and relax | First Drive | Autocar India
description: The Mercedes-Benz S-Class has long been the default choice of luxury limousine for India's mega rich. This all-new seventh-gen model promises to offer the all the comfort you could possibly want and also comes packed to the roof with tech. Renuka Kirpalani gives her review from the back seat while Nikhil Bhatia plays chauffeur for the day.

title: Mercedes-Maybach GLS 600 review - Dancing with the star! | First Drive | Autocar India
description: What better way to celebrate 600 million views than with a review of the Mercedes-Maybach GLS 600! Maybach grandiose meets SUV versatility in the uber-luxury Mercedes-Maybach GLS 600. Shapur Kotwal tells you what makes it so very special.

title: Ferrari Roma India review - Bellissimo! | First Drive | Autocar India
description: Long, low and loud, the Roma is everything you'd want a Ferrari GT to be. Shapur Kotwal has a memorable afternoon of coffee and cars.

title: 2021 Mercedes-Benz S 350d review - What's the locally assembled S like? | First Drive| Autocar India
description: The latest-gen Mercedes-Benz S-Class is now assembled in India. Gavin D'Souza tells you how it's different to the fully imported Launch Edition model and if this new S 350d is all the S-Class you need.

title: 2021 Jaguar F-Pace review - Inside job | First Drive | Autocar India
description: The Jaguar F-Pace is fresh from an update. Gavin d'Souza reacquaints you with the charming Jag SUV, shows you what's new and tells you why you can't ignore one any longer.

title: 2021 Mercedes-Benz E-Class review - Star performer | First Drive | Autocar India
description: The Mercedes-Benz E-Class is fresh from an update. Nikhil Bhatia tells you what's new and what the range-topping E 350d is like.

title: 2021 Volvo XC60 review - Swede Sensation | First Drive | Autocar India
description: The Volvo XC60 has received an update, and while the changes might seem subtle, they are significant as Jay Patil finds out.

title: 2022 Volvo S90 - Stately Affair | First Drive | Autocar India
description: Volvo's flagship sedan has been updated with a new heart among other premium additions. Shapur Kotwal finds out how much has it changed the S90.

title: Porsche Taycan review - It's electric and electrifying! | First Drive | Autocar India
description: Does the all-electric Porsche drive like a Porsche should? Shapur Kotwal finds out.
